      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah the db_conn_wait is definitely the main thing. but it's weird because the traffic volume hasn't actually increased during those spikes. it's like it just randomly hits a wall and the connections all tie up for no reason. any idea why it would happen intermittently like that if the load is steady?",
